title: Luvvies sign letter protesting scrapping of refugee scheme
text: show ad Luvvies on the march as Lineker, Knightley and Cumberbatch sign letter complaining at PM's 'disgraceful' scrapping of child refugee scheme Open letter accuses Thereas May of being 'truly shameful' after Government announced closure of scheme to resettle child migrants More than 200 leading public figures sign letter demanding the PM rethink Other names include Emma Thompson, Gok Wan, Jude Law and Paloma Faith
